<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id52c3af10-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s1911"><num value="1911">§ 1911.</num><heading> Supreme Court</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Supreme Court may fix the fees to be charged by its clerk.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The fees of the clerk, cost of serving process, and other necessary disbursements incidental to any case before the court, may be taxed against the litigants as the court directs.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id52c3af11-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/954">62 Stat. 954</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id52c3af12-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id52c3af13-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 330 (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s223">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 223</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1153">36 Stat. 1153</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The second paragraph was inserted to give statutory sanction to existing practice.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes were made in phraseology.</p>
</note>
</notes>
